@startuml Session_Validation_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title Session Validation Process (Cookie-First Authentication)

actor User as U
participant "Frontend\n(blog.localtest.me:3000)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

== Authentication Check Request ==
U -> FE: 1. Navigate to protected page
note right: User accesses application

FE -> BE: 2. GET /auth/me (credentials: include)
note right
**Request Details:**
- Method: GET
- URL: api.localtest.me:3001/auth/me
- Credentials: include (automatic cookies)
- Headers: Content-Type: application/json

**No Authorization header needed**
Browser automatically includes cookies
end note

== Session Extraction (Cookie-First Priority) ==
BE -> BE: 3. Extract session with priority system
note right
**Session Extraction Priority:**

```typescript
// 1. PRIMARY: HTTP-only cookie (preferred)
const cookieName = "astral_session";
if (cookie && cookie[cookieName]?.value) {
  sessionId = cookie[cookieName].value;
}

// 2. FALLBACK: Authorization header
if (!sessionId && headers.authorization) {
  sessionId = headers.authorization.replace("Bearer ", "");
}

// 3. FINAL FALLBACK: X-Session-ID header
if (!sessionId && headers["x-session-id"]) {
  sessionId = headers["x-session-id"];
}
```

**Why Cookie-First?**
- More secure (HTTP-only)
- Automatic browser handling
- XSS attack protection
- No manual header management
end note

alt Session ID extracted successfully
    BE -> DB: 4a. Validate session in database
    note right
    **Session Validation Query:**
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      s.*,                          -- Session data
      u.id as user_id, 
      u.email, 
      u.name, 
      u.picture,
      p.provider_name               -- OAuth provider
    FROM sessions s
    JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.id
    JOIN providers p ON u.provider_id = p.id
    WHERE s.id = $1                 -- Match session ID
    AND s.expires_at > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  -- Not expired
    ```
    
    **Validation Checks:**
    1. Session exists in database
    2. Session not expired (expires_at > NOW())
    3. User record linked and valid
    4. Provider information available
    end note
    
    alt Session valid and not expired
        DB -> BE: 5a. Return complete user data
        note right
        **Database Response:**
        ```json
        {
          "id": "session-123",
          "user_id": "uuid-456", 
          "access_token": "discord-token",
          "refresh_token": "discord-refresh",
          "expires_at": "2024-02-01T12:00:00Z",
          "email": "user@example.com",
          "name": "Display Name",
          "picture": "avatar-url",
          "provider_name": "discord"
        }
        ```
        end note
        
        BE -> FE: 6a. Return authenticated user
        note right
        **Success Response:**
        ```json
        {
          "user": {
            "id": "uuid-456",
            "email": "user@example.com", 
            "name": "Display Name",
            "picture": "avatar-url",
            "provider": "discord"
          }
        }
        ```
        
        **HTTP Status:** 200 OK
        end note
        
        FE -> U: 7a. Show authenticated interface
        note right
        **Frontend Actions:**
        1. Store user data in Pinia store
        2. Update UI to authenticated state
        3. Show user profile/avatar
        4. Enable protected features
        end note
        
    else Session expired or invalid
        DB -> BE: 5b. No session found / expired
        note right
        **Possible Scenarios:**
        1. Session ID not in database
        2. Session expired (expires_at < NOW())
        3. User record deleted
        4. Database connection issues
        end note
        
        BE -> FE: 6b. Return authentication error
        note right
        **Error Response:**
        ```json
        {
          "error": "Session not found in database",
          "sessionId": "session-123"
        }
        ```
        
        **HTTP Status:** 401 Unauthorized
        end note
        
        FE -> FE: 7b. Clear invalid session state
        note right
        **Frontend Error Handling:**
        1. Clear user data from Pinia store
        2. Clear any cached authentication state
        3. Reset UI to unauthenticated state
        end note
        
        FE -> U: 8b. Redirect to login page
        note right: User must re-authenticate
    end
    
else No session ID found
    BE -> FE: 4b. Return no session error
    note right
    **Error Response:**
    ```json
    {
      "error": "No session found",
      "debug": {
        "cookieReceived": false,
        "authHeaderReceived": false, 
        "sessionHeaderReceived": false
      }
    }
    ```
    
    **Common Causes:**
    1. User never logged in
    2. Cookie expired/deleted
    3. Different domain/subdomain
    4. Browser cookie disabled
    end note
    
    FE -> U: 5b. Show login interface
    note right: User sees unauthenticated state
end

== Session Usage in Protected Routes ==
note over BE
**Once session is validated, it's available for:**

1. **Route Protection:** Middleware checks session
2. **User Context:** Access to user ID and profile
3. **API Authorization:** Discord token for external calls
4. **Audit Logging:** Track user actions
5. **Personalization:** User-specific content

**Session Data Available:**
- User UUID for database queries
- Discord access/refresh tokens
- User profile information
- Provider information
end note

== Automatic Session Refresh (Future) ==
note over BE, DB
**Potential Enhancement:**

When session nears expiration:
1. Check if refresh_token exists
2. Call Discord token refresh endpoint
3. Update session with new tokens
4. Extend session expiration
5. Return updated session to client

**Benefits:**
- Seamless user experience
- No re-authentication needed
- Maintains security boundaries
end note

@enduml
